simple django app

libraries to install:
sudo apt-get install  python-dev
sudo apt-get install  libpq-dev
sudo apt-get install  python-pip
sudo apt-get install  git

setup DB here with db name=django_db
http://blog.iiilx.com/programming/how-to-install-postgres-on-ubuntu-for-django/
Note: pg_hba.conf is here: not 1 level higher like the blogpost: /etc/postgresql/9.1/main/pg_hba.conf

init db:
python manage.py syncdb

start django:
python manage.py runserver 

How2 login to AWS:
ssh bitnami@54.247.113.119 -i andy2.pem 

# Using this stack on AWS:
http://bitnami.org/stack/djangostack#cloudImage

# restart Apache:
sudo ./ctlscript.sh restart apache
